+**FINAL correct `findEarliestSlot`:**
+
+```typescript
+function findEarliestSlot(
+  roomAssignments: Assignment[],
+  earliestStart: number,
+  duration: number,
+  gap: number,
+  endTime: number
+): number | null {
+  let candidate = earliestStart;
+
+  for (const existing of roomAssignments) {
+    // Can we fit before this existing event (with gap)?
+    if (candidate + duration + gap <= existing.startTime) {
+      break;
+    }
+    // Move past this existing event (with gap after it)
+    candidate = Math.max(candidate, existing.endTime + gap);
+  }
+
+  if (candidate + duration <= endTime) {
+    return candidate;
+  }
+  return null;
+}
+```
+
+Note: The gap between events in the same room means: `eventA.endTime + gap <= eventB.startTime`. So when checking if we fit before an existing event: `candidate + duration + gap <= existing.startTime`. When skipping past: `candidate = existing.endTime + gap`.
